                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ærgom" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ærgom</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ærgon</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>лицо</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>face</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>лицевая, передняя часть</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>facing part, fore-part</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>очевидный</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>evident</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>явный</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>obvious</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>открытый</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>open</q></tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ærgomæj</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>открыто</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>overtly</q></tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ærgom kænyn</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>делать явным</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to make obvious</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>выявлять</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>reveal</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>открывать</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>discover</q></tr></sense></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>de ʽrgom næm ma razdax</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>не обращай к нам лица</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>do not turn your face to us</q></tr></example><example><quote>q˳yddag rаrgom īs</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>дело раскрылось</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the case was solved</q></tr></example><example><quote>Nartæn sæ žwar ærgom rašydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Нартовское божество открыто вышло (к народу)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Nart divinity overtly came to people</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I 179</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ærgom ʒyrdy kʼæm næj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в откровенной речи нет ничего зазорного</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>there is nothing shameful in a frank speech</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 237</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ærgomæj saxarmæ nal cydī</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>не мог уже явно войти в город</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[Jesus] could no more openly enter into the city</q></tr><bibl><biblScope>Марк 1 45</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>axæm sūsæg nīcy īs, ḱī næ rargom wa</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>нет ничего тайного, что не сделалось бы явным</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>for there is nothing hid, which shall not be manifested</q></tr><bibl><biblScope>Марк 4 22</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>æxe næmæ næ sirgon kænʒænæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он нам не откроется</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he will not open to us</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>34%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>Batraz Boræfærnugmæ je ʽrgon raxatgæj ʒoruj...</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Батраз, повернувшись лицом к Борафарнугу, говорит...</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Facing Borafarnug, Batraz says…</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>mах dær zæǧʒystæm ærgom</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мы тоже скажем открыто</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>we will also say frankly</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 65</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>de ʽrgom næm ma razdax</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>не обращай к нам лица</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>do not turn your face to us</q></tr></example><example><quote>q˳yddag rаrgom īs</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>дело раскрылось</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the case was solved</q></tr></example><example><quote>Nartæn sæ žwar ærgom rašydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Нартовское божество открыто вышло (к народу)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Nart divinity overtly came to people</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I 179</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ærgom ʒyrdy kʼæm næj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в откровенной речи нет ничего зазорного</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>there is nothing shameful in a frank speech</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 237</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ærgomæj saxarmæ nal cydī</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>не мог уже явно войти в город</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[Jesus] could no more openly enter into the city</q></tr><bibl><biblScope>Марк 1 45</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>axæm sūsæg nīcy īs, ḱī næ rargom wa</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>нет ничего тайного, что не сделалось бы явным</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>for there is nothing hid, which shall not be manifested</q></tr><bibl><biblScope>Марк 4 22</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>æxe næmæ næ sirgon kænʒænæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он нам не откроется</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he will not open to us</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>34%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>Batraz Boræfærnugmæ je ʽrgon raxatgæj ʒoruj...</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Батраз, повернувшись лицом к Борафарнугу, говорит...</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Facing Borafarnug, Batraz says…</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>mах dær zæǧʒystæm ærgom</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мы тоже скажем открыто</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>we will also say frankly</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 65</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Сращение префикса %iær%i- с <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/> ‘рот’ (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæskom"/> ‘лицо’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gom"/> gom ‘открытый’). Префикс %iær%i-, весьма употребительный в качестве живого преверба (ср. %iær-gom kænyn%i ‘обнажить’), в старых сращениях известен лишь в немногих случаях; кроме %iærgom%i ср. в особенности <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtax"/> ‘капля’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtæx"/> ‘роса’ и д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtajun"/> ‘купаться’. С <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>ær-gom</w></mentioned> можно сопоставить <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>an-kam-</w></mentioned> в %i’nkm’ny%i ‘открыто’, ‘в лицо’, от *%ikam%i ‘рот’, ‘лицо’, но с другим префиксом (%ian%i- из %iham%i). См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gom"/>. Для семантики (‘явный’ — ‘лицо’) ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>čiϑra-</w></mentioned> 1. ‘явный’, 2. ‘лицо’. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>а̀rgama</w> <gloss><q>явно</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘гласно’ (<bibl><biblScope>%bХр. Вост. V 192%b</biblScope></bibl>) и <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/> <w>argam</w></mentioned> id. представляют, очевидно, старое заимствование из осетинского (аланского). Ср. д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_irux"/> irux.%n<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JA"/><biblScope>1936, стр. 202—203</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The fusion of the prefix %iær%i- with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/> ‘mouth’ (compare <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæskom"/> ‘face’ and<ref type="xr" target="#entry_gom"/> gom ‘open’). The prefix %iær%i-, which is quite common as a modern preverb (compare %iær-gom kænyn%i ‘to bare’), is known just in few ancient fusions; besides %iærgom%i especially compare <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtax"/> ‘drop’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtæx"/> ‘dew’ and Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtajun"/> ‘to bath’. One may compare the following with <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>ær-gom</w></mentioned> : <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>an-kam-</w></mentioned> in %i’nkm’ny%i ‘overtly’, ‘frankly’, from *%ikam%i ‘mouth’, ‘face’, but with another prefix (%ian%i- from %iham%i). See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gom"/>. As for semantics (‘overt’ — ‘face’), compare <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>čiϑra-</w></mentioned> 1. ‘overt’, 2. ‘face’. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>а̀rgama</w> <gloss><q>overtly</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘openly’ (<bibl><biblScope>Xristianskij vostok, vol. 192</biblScope></bibl>) and <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/> <w>argam</w></mentioned> id. represent apparently ancient borrowing from Ossetic (Alan). Compare Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_irux"/>.%n<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JA"/><biblScope>1936, стр. 202—203</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>